'''Helga Gitmark''' (born [[30 September]] [[1929]] in [[Holt, Norway|Holt]]) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] politician for the [[Centre Party (Norway)|Centre Party]].

She was the Minister of the Environment from March to October 1973 during the [[cabinet Korvald]].

She served in the position of deputy representative to the [[Stortinget|Norwegian Parliament]] from [[Aust-Agder]] during the term 1977&ndash;1981. On the local level she was member of [[Lillesand]] municipality council during the terms 1971&ndash;1975 and 1991&ndash;1995.

In addition she was a member of the board in several organizations within the [[Church of Norway]], as well as other Christian organizations.

